{"id":801122497,"question_id":13,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 year, 9 months","timestamp":1663315803,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"7 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/801122497/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"45.1 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int romanToInt(String s) {\n        \n        int[] arr = new int[s.length()];\n        for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){\n            char c = s.charAt(i);\n            \n            if(c=='I')  arr[i]=1;\n            if(c=='V')  arr[i]=5;\n            if(c=='X')  arr[i]=10;\n            if(c=='L')  arr[i]=50;\n            if(c=='C')  arr[i]=100;\n            if(c=='D')  arr[i]=500;\n            if(c=='M')  arr[i]=1000;\n        }\n        \n        int res=0;\n        for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){\n            if(i<arr.length-1 && arr[i]<arr[i+1]){\n                res+=-arr[i];\n            }else{\n                res+=arr[i];\n            }\n        }\n        \n        \n        return res;\n        \n        \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
